sentences: Jaddanbai Hussain was born around 1892 to Miajaan and Daleepabai, one of chilbila, Meja Allahabad's most renowned dancers.
Shrimant Ganpat Rao died in 1920 while she was still a student, so she completed her training under Ustad Moinuddin Khan.
She later began acting when the Play Art Photo Tone Company of Lahore approached her for a role in their movie Raja Gopichand in 1933.
The company produced Talashe Haq in 1935, in which she acted and composed the music.
In 1936 she acted in, directed, and wrote the music for Madam Fashion.
Jaddanbai Hussain (1892 – 8 April 1949; known professionally as Jaddanbai) was an Indian singer, music composer, dancer, actress, filmmaker, and one of the pioneers of Indian cinema.
Abdul Rashid spent most of his days idle, with Jaddanbai being the main breadwinner during their time together.
